# Top-level runtime dependency for the action's container image.
#
# This is the ecs CLI from our hardened fork of fabfuel/ecs-deploy, pinned
# to a 40-character commit SHA. Pinning at the SHA level is content-
# addressed: the install spec itself names the exact source tree, so even
# if the branch tip moves, this build doesn't.
#
# The fully-pinned, hashed lockfile (with hashes for ALL transitive deps
# like boto3, click, requests, etc.) is `requirements.txt`, generated by:
#
#   CUTOFF="$(date -v-7d +%Y-%m-%d)"   # macOS
#   # CUTOFF="$(date -d '7 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d)"   # Linux
#   uv pip compile requirements.in \
#     --python-version 3.13 \
#     --generate-hashes \
#     --exclude-newer "$CUTOFF" \
#     --output-file requirements.txt
#
# The cooldown (`--exclude-newer`) is a 7-day supply-chain delay: we don't
# pull a brand-new transitive package until it has been in the wild for at
# least a week. CVE-driven exceptions use `--exclude-newer-package` per
# the gfi-mcp pattern.
#
# To bump the fabfuel pin: replace the SHA below, re-run the compile
# command, and review the resulting requirements.txt diff.

# ignitetech-group/ecs-deploy @ release tag 2026.5
# https://github.com/ignitetech-group/ecs-deploy/releases/tag/2026.5
ecs-deploy @ git+https://github.com/ignitetech-group/ecs-deploy@9890ee4fb53cce5266705959e69b22d38b0e1120
